WEBVTT

00:01.314 --> 00:01.748
you

04:53.794 --> 04:57.698
So many of you have been waiting for that all year long, and it's here.

04:57.758 --> 05:02.123
What has become just our kickoff really into the Christmas season.

05:02.143 --> 05:03.625
It's become tradition around here.

05:03.665 --> 05:06.408
We couldn't go December without Carol the Bells.

05:07.349 --> 05:08.330
Come on, ridiculous.

05:08.911 --> 05:09.612
What happens here?

05:09.632 --> 05:11.614
And we're going to take a hard right turn, though.

05:11.854 --> 05:13.716
And we're going to begin a time of worship together.

05:13.736 --> 05:15.599
And so I want to invite all of you to stand with us.

05:16.419 --> 05:18.642
Wherever you're joining us, we're so glad you're here with us.

05:18.662 --> 05:21.705
But I'm going to kick it off to Jeremy and the team to lead us in this time of worship.

05:21.725 --> 05:22.226
Thanks, everybody.

20:19.362 --> 20:30.740
So thankful for who you are to us, Lord, for the love that you have for us, for the hope that can be found when we put our trust in you, Jesus.

20:33.445 --> 20:43.400
And Jesus, I'm thankful that no matter what we came in here with, where we find ourselves today, thankful that our circumstances don't determine your goodness.

20:43.461 --> 20:44.402
That's just who you are.

20:49.922 --> 20:54.591
reminded of that truth today, that you are good, you are faithful to us in every season.

20:56.315 --> 20:58.339
So Jesus, we give this time to you.

20:58.359 --> 21:00.102
Would you be glorified in this place?

21:00.182 --> 21:01.345
You are worthy of our praise.

21:01.405 --> 21:03.870
You're worthy of all the worship that we could ever give.

21:04.792 --> 21:05.253
We love you.

21:05.293 --> 21:06.856
We pray this all in your powerful name.

21:07.637 --> 21:08.158
Amen.

21:08.980 --> 21:09.401
Amen.

21:09.421 --> 21:10.904
Everybody, so good to be with you.

21:10.924 --> 21:11.986
You can take a seat.

21:17.058 --> 21:17.719
Well, hey, everybody.

21:18.099 --> 21:23.126
It's truly great to see you join us right here in the room and wherever you might be joining us online.

21:23.146 --> 21:25.249
I'm so glad that you chose to be here with us this weekend.

21:25.269 --> 21:27.552
I don't think there's any better place that you could be.

21:27.693 --> 21:33.400
And I really believe that it's a special weekend that you showed up on number one, because we kicked off our service with Carol the Bells.

21:33.821 --> 21:35.083
And that's always a fun one.

21:35.643 --> 21:38.507
But I also got to say, I wish the guys would make it look a little harder.

21:38.968 --> 21:40.670
They make playing guitar look so easy.

21:40.690 --> 21:41.531
Like, I could go do that.

21:41.692 --> 21:43.474
And I couldn't.

21:43.778 --> 21:44.319
It's awesome.

21:44.439 --> 21:44.779
It's awesome.

21:44.799 --> 21:51.065
But the other reason why it's a special weekend is because this weekend, 20 years ago, we opened the doors to the Lionel Lakes campus.

21:51.826 --> 21:53.007
It's absolutely incredible.

21:53.027 --> 21:53.687
Can you believe that?

21:54.248 --> 21:57.571
And I know many of you, you remember that moment.

21:57.591 --> 22:00.614
You remember, this was what Eagle Brook was supposed to be.

22:00.694 --> 22:01.195
This was it.

22:01.715 --> 22:03.677
It was just supposed to be this location.

22:03.737 --> 22:07.020
We shut down the original location in White Bear.

22:07.040 --> 22:10.744
We moved into this building in 2005, thinking this was going to be it.

22:11.464 --> 22:13.106
And within a month, we were at capacity.

22:13.538 --> 22:18.203
And so we had to reopen the White Bear Lake location and became a multi-site church.

22:18.804 --> 22:25.471
Now, 20 years later, we have 14 locations and online, all over Minnesota, all over the world that people are experiencing.

22:26.011 --> 22:26.532
Come on.

22:29.355 --> 22:38.585
And I was recently reading an email from a longtime attender who was here days before the campus was supposed to open, praying for this building, praying for the people that are going to walk through this door.

22:38.625 --> 22:39.826
And here's what he said.

22:40.290 --> 22:50.707
He said, I remember praying, asking God to reach untold hundreds who never knew the Lord before, out in the middle of a cornfield where no one ever expected to see a church.

22:51.649 --> 22:59.822
That prayer for hundreds actually has become over 9,000 people who have put their faith in Christ through an experience at the Lionel Lakes campus alone.

23:00.523 --> 23:02.066
And then beyond that,

23:02.146 --> 23:11.034
We in 2017 launched online church, and so the life-changing message of Jesus has gone beyond these walls, beyond the ways that we could ever imagine or even expect.

23:11.114 --> 23:15.759
And I know that many of you are here because of an experience like that.

23:16.379 --> 23:21.284
And aren't you glad that we worship and serve a God that goes beyond what we think is supposed to be?

23:22.265 --> 23:22.505
Yeah.

23:23.286 --> 23:27.910
And some of you are here after living and wondering, is my life more than my addiction?

23:28.811 --> 23:31.954
Is life more than my diagnosis?

23:32.066 --> 23:39.136
infertility that I'm experiencing, my failed marriage, bad decisions that I've made throughout my lifetime, or just being far from God.

23:39.736 --> 23:41.719
But you've discovered that God has more for your life.

23:42.520 --> 23:52.153
And Ephesians 3.20 says this, now to him who is able to do it measurably more than we can ask or imagine according to his power at work within us, to him be the glory.

23:52.173 --> 23:58.642
And so we are celebrating this weekend of 20 years of faithfulness.

23:59.394 --> 24:13.047
We're celebrating 20 years of God answering prayers and invitations that have gone out of this place and logging obedience in the same direction as we continue to listen to where God's calling us and as you continue to invite people to experience the life changing message of Jesus.

24:13.727 --> 24:17.451
So that's what we're celebrating is we turn the corner to the future and look ahead.

24:17.651 --> 24:21.895
I wonder, is there somebody in your life that needs to know that there's more to their life?

24:22.656 --> 24:24.397
There's more than just what they're experiencing now.

24:24.437 --> 24:29.362
God has more for them than they could ever ask or imagine and you need to invite that person to church.

24:29.634 --> 24:31.557
I want to challenge you to do that over these next few weeks.

24:31.577 --> 24:33.441
I've got a couple of opportunities for that to happen.

24:33.501 --> 24:36.005
The first is for students, middle school and high school students.

24:36.065 --> 24:40.594
We've got the biggest party of the entire year this coming Wednesday across all of our locations.

24:41.255 --> 24:45.402
That if you're in driving distance of one of those, get your middle school, get your high schooler to that party.

24:45.763 --> 24:47.646
Festival of Festiveness is happening.

24:48.107 --> 24:52.114
Middle school and high school are together, 630 to 830, but invite those students.

24:52.162 --> 24:52.683
and get them here.

24:52.723 --> 24:54.987
But the next opportunity is our Christmas services.

24:55.507 --> 24:59.113
In just a week and a half or two weeks, whatever it is, we're starting Christmas services.

24:59.534 --> 25:06.164
Here at the Lionel Lakes campus, we've got seven different moments, different services, and five of those are gonna be broadcast online.

25:06.184 --> 25:14.418
So there's somebody in your life that they'll be able to make it to one of those experiences, or if you send them the link, they'll be able to experience the online experience.

25:14.438 --> 25:19.666
So get them there, invite and let's see what God does and see the more that he has for them.

25:19.906 --> 25:24.031
But this weekend, as we look to hear from Jason and continue our series, all is not calm.

25:24.071 --> 25:29.018
It wouldn't be a celebration or a party without a party favor and a cake.

25:29.519 --> 25:35.547
And so as you leave today, we've got birthday themed flavored dumb dums that you can grab as you leave.

25:35.607 --> 25:41.234
So grab, grab one of those birthday cake, cotton candy, grab one of those as you leave, but also we've got a cake and it's a video cake.

25:42.050 --> 25:45.762
But what I need you to do on the count of three, would you just help me yell happy birthday?

25:45.782 --> 25:49.173
And then we're going to see a video of the recapping the last 20 years of all that God has done.

25:49.193 --> 25:50.397
But let's do this together.

25:50.497 --> 25:51.280
One, two, three.

25:51.340 --> 25:53.808
Happy birthday.

25:53.828 --> 25:54.450
Thanks, everybody.

26:06.786 --> 26:11.353
Jesus said, I will build my church and the gates of hell will not prevail against it.

26:11.433 --> 26:14.157
What a moment.

26:14.177 --> 26:15.319
What a miracle this is.

26:15.339 --> 26:21.489
20 years ago, we opened this building with a simple prayer.

26:21.989 --> 26:25.274
God, would you use this church to reach people far from you?

26:26.076 --> 26:32.546
That was the vision, to be known as a community built on prayer, worship, serving, and loving others.

26:33.127 --> 26:35.410
And from day one, God answered our prayers.

26:35.874 --> 26:38.837
Over 8,000 people came to church that first weekend.

26:39.498 --> 26:46.404
Week after week, people met God through worship, teaching, and the love that they felt when they walked through the door.

26:46.424 --> 26:51.249
Even though Lionel Lakes wasn't our first building, it sparked a new beginning in our mission to reach others.

26:51.589 --> 26:55.133
And it became the home base for our messages each week.

26:55.153 --> 27:02.160
Every inch of this building, from the lobby to the kids' faces to the worship center, was designed to point people to Jesus.

27:02.840 --> 27:04.562
Every story of transformation

27:04.770 --> 27:08.959
is a reminder of God's faithfulness, and there's so much more to come.

27:10.081 --> 27:17.377
As we look into the future, we trust God to lead the way, because God loves people, and this is His church.

27:24.592 --> 27:25.394
Yeah, go ahead.

27:30.882 --> 27:34.487
It is the 20-year anniversary of our Lionel Lake's campus.

27:34.527 --> 27:40.174
And if you're at one of our other campuses or you're relatively new to maybe Eagle Brook, you may not know this, but we started at White Bear Lake.

27:40.755 --> 27:45.661
And then the leadership at that time and the entire church risked everything to build this building.

27:46.402 --> 27:50.808
They risked careers, they risked the future of our church to build this building.

27:50.888 --> 27:55.634
And then by God's power and God's grace, shortly after we opened, it was full.

27:56.450 --> 28:01.937
And so we still owned the White Bear Lake building and we thought, okay, well, what if we just open that as a video venue of sorts?

28:02.638 --> 28:04.240
And that's how multi-site was born.

28:04.260 --> 28:05.882
That's how we kind of stumbled into it.

28:05.903 --> 28:08.326
So if you're at a campus right now, that's where it started.

28:08.346 --> 28:16.356
It's hard with White Bear Lake and Lionel Lakes, but we are celebrating and thanking God for 20 years of ministry in this building.

28:16.897 --> 28:20.502
A few weeks ago, or a few weeks ago, rather, our family visited the Brainer Lakes campus.

28:21.023 --> 28:23.666
And Don Wicklin, who's the campus pastor there, got up.

28:24.002 --> 28:27.606
and shared that Christmas has not always been a happy time for her family.

28:28.667 --> 28:33.913
She talked about a season when her brother passed away tragically, her dad died shortly after that.

28:35.055 --> 28:39.580
And she said that Christmas was this reminder that life had changed.

28:40.621 --> 28:42.723
We're in a series right now called All Is Not Calm.

28:43.724 --> 28:44.966
And we sing that around this season.

28:44.986 --> 28:52.274
We sing, all is calm, all is bright, but maybe in your life, all is not calm and all is not bright.

28:53.698 --> 29:04.168
Our prayer and our hope in this series is that God would use this series to restore our souls and to prepare us to celebrate the birth of Jesus Christ.

29:04.829 --> 29:10.134
I was reading a story a few months ago about a couple that had fed their baby Mountain Dew instead of milk.

29:11.835 --> 29:12.916
This is a weird story.

29:13.196 --> 29:17.901
But they confronted the mom about this and they said, how come you kept giving your baby Mountain Dew?

29:17.921 --> 29:19.362
And this was the mom's exact quote.

29:19.643 --> 29:23.346
She said, once the baby tasted Mountain Dew, he didn't want milk anymore.

29:25.026 --> 29:32.056
Now I realize this raises all kinds of questions about parenting and stupidity and maybe all kinds of other questions that you might have.

29:33.097 --> 29:46.896
But I wonder if there is a spiritual analogy in that story that for some of us today, our souls have been feeding on Mountain Dew instead of the spiritual milk that we need for nourishment.

29:47.797 --> 29:48.658
What do I mean by that?

29:49.346 --> 29:51.649
Our brains crave dopamine.

29:51.689 --> 29:55.473
Dopamine is the feel-good chemical, and you can get dopamine from a lot of different things.

29:55.514 --> 30:00.399
I mean, if someone likes your post on social media, you get a shot of dopamine from that.

30:00.960 --> 30:04.725
That's why they've created that function on social media, because it keeps you coming back.

30:05.566 --> 30:08.189
This is why pornography is so addictive.

30:09.110 --> 30:15.137
When we view pornography, maybe without even realizing it, dopamine is released into our brains.

30:16.299 --> 30:18.962
And so your brain starts to go, oh, I'll give me more of that.

30:20.098 --> 30:22.923
But it's never enough, it's more, it's more, it's more.

30:23.163 --> 30:26.809
And the next thing you know, you are addicted to destructive behaviors.

30:27.971 --> 30:30.695
And it's not just pornography that creates that phenomenon.

30:30.715 --> 30:36.325
There's many things that cause us to become addicted to the next dopamine high.

30:37.126 --> 30:46.962
In Ephesians chapter four, verse 19, the Apostle Paul is speaking to people whose hearts have been hardened because of repeated sin in their life.

30:48.002 --> 30:58.573
He says, having lost all sensitivity, they have given themselves over to sensuality so as to indulge in every kind of impurity.

31:00.215 --> 31:02.117
He says, they've lost all sensitivity.

31:03.418 --> 31:07.222
This is like when you go to the dentist and they give you a shot of Novocaine and it's just numb.

31:07.282 --> 31:09.224
You can't feel anything.

31:10.065 --> 31:14.930
There are people in America today who have become desensitized to sin.

31:16.354 --> 31:17.956
They've lost all sensitivity.

31:18.217 --> 31:21.181
It's not like they're sinning and then they're going, oh, I feel guilty about that.

31:21.201 --> 31:22.623
I'm so sorry, God.

31:22.663 --> 31:23.485
They're numb to it.

31:24.626 --> 31:26.028
They're desensitized to it.

31:27.310 --> 31:30.916
Paul says they've given themselves over to sensuality.

31:30.976 --> 31:31.957
Why do they do that?

31:33.419 --> 31:34.521
Because it feels good.

31:34.621 --> 31:36.043
It's a shot of dopamine.

31:36.324 --> 31:38.347
Spiritually speaking, it's Mountain Dew.

31:39.769 --> 31:46.098
But it's not giving them the spiritual milk that their soul needs for nourishment in her book, Soul Care.

31:46.914 --> 31:48.937
Author Deborah Folletta asked this.

31:48.957 --> 31:57.951
She says, when we start feeling even the slightest hint of emptiness, drain and exhaustion, we can be tempted to run to a quick fix.

31:59.113 --> 32:05.142
Something to give us a boost, distract us, or fill us up as fast as possible.

32:06.985 --> 32:07.826
What is that for you?

32:09.570 --> 32:18.203
When you are feeling empty, when you are feeling drained, when you're feeling just a little down and melancholy, what is that thing in your life that you go, oh, I just wanna do that.

32:19.926 --> 32:21.128
I just need some of that.

32:23.151 --> 32:25.775
Might be opening up a certain app and just scrolling.

32:25.835 --> 32:28.199
It might be going back to a destructive relationship.

32:29.821 --> 32:33.106
Might be working more hours and just throwing yourself into your work.

32:33.126 --> 32:35.810
But what do you turn to when you feel drained?

32:36.892 --> 32:38.194
Pastor Timothy Keller,

32:38.466 --> 32:42.692
author and pastor in New York, he once asked this question, he said, all people seek happiness.

32:43.954 --> 32:44.755
And that is very true.

32:45.877 --> 32:48.561
Me, all of us, we all want to be happy in some way.

32:48.581 --> 32:52.187
He said, and they attach themselves to things they believe will make them happy.

32:53.489 --> 32:59.317
So we see something, we think, oh yeah, that's gonna make me happy, I'm gonna attach myself to that, I'm gonna do that, but here's the problem.

33:00.259 --> 33:05.106
He says, the main human problem, however, is that because of sin,

33:05.218 --> 33:08.421
We misidentify what will make us happy.

33:10.403 --> 33:13.567
In other words, we look at something, we go, oh, I'm not doing great right now.

33:13.847 --> 33:14.648
I'm feeling down.

33:14.688 --> 33:15.929
I'm feeling drained right now.

33:16.129 --> 33:17.711
But if I do that, then I'll be happy.

33:19.152 --> 33:27.241
But because of the effects of sin on our hearts and our minds, we misidentify what is going to make us happy.

33:28.782 --> 33:32.626
What is it that you think is going to make you happy?

33:33.474 --> 33:37.701
In Psalm 42, King David asks this question, he says to his own soul.

33:37.741 --> 33:39.804
He's asking his own soul.

33:40.104 --> 33:45.993
He says, why are you cast down, oh my soul, and why are you in turmoil within me?

33:47.996 --> 33:53.044
Strikes me that David was able to identify how his soul was feeling.

33:53.265 --> 33:55.208
And he says, my soul is downcast.

33:56.790 --> 33:57.671
And maybe that's you today.

33:59.574 --> 34:01.938
Maybe all is not calm, all is not bright.

34:03.234 --> 34:07.099
that there's something in your soul that feels down.

34:07.119 --> 34:11.245
I wanna show you three ways that God can restore your soul.

34:11.285 --> 34:13.048
The first one is this, slow down.

34:14.930 --> 34:15.551
Slow down.

34:17.013 --> 34:19.677
I've been studying Psalm 23 for the last month.

34:20.799 --> 34:24.584
If by the way, if you've never memorized Psalm 23, I would encourage you to do this.

34:25.225 --> 34:28.850
My six-year-old daughter has this better memorized than I do.

34:29.506 --> 34:30.668
So she can memorize it.

34:30.788 --> 34:31.589
I can memorize it.

34:31.850 --> 34:32.711
You can memorize it.

34:32.751 --> 34:33.593
It's so deep.

34:33.673 --> 34:34.334
It's so rich.

34:34.755 --> 34:36.197
Here's how King David begins.

34:37.159 --> 34:39.022
He says, the Lord is my shepherd.

34:40.464 --> 34:41.386
I shall not want.

34:42.888 --> 34:45.532
He makes me lie down in green pastures.

34:45.833 --> 34:48.257
He leads me besides still waters.

34:48.718 --> 34:51.142
He restores my soul.

34:52.824 --> 34:54.207
Here's the word I don't want you to miss.

34:55.309 --> 34:56.210
It's the word Lord.

34:57.570 --> 34:59.032
See, we've just tempted to pass over that.

34:59.052 --> 35:05.261
It doesn't seem like really that big of a deal in the scope of the whole sentence, but he says that the Lord is His shepherd.

35:06.463 --> 35:09.047
It's not noteworthy that sheep would have a shepherd.

35:09.487 --> 35:10.389
All sheep do.

35:11.150 --> 35:16.057
In fact, all human beings have something or someone that they're following with their life.

35:17.058 --> 35:25.170
Now, if you've ever thought about this, but even an atheist has someone or something that they follow, oftentimes themselves, but we all have a shepherd.

35:25.762 --> 35:29.407
David says, my shepherd is the Lord God.

35:30.308 --> 35:34.454
And because it's the Lord God, I shall not want.

35:35.415 --> 35:36.236
I want all the time.

35:37.418 --> 35:41.704
You probably want all the time as well because we live in a world of want.

35:42.565 --> 35:44.127
Every day, all around us want.

35:45.229 --> 35:46.170
I want a better body.

35:46.190 --> 35:47.792
I want better health.

35:48.052 --> 35:52.178
I want a better job, better salary, better grades, better relationships.

35:53.026 --> 35:58.733
We live in a world of want and into that world.

35:59.614 --> 36:02.959
King David says, I shall not want.

36:04.020 --> 36:04.280
Why?

36:05.963 --> 36:07.985
Because if he has God, he has everything he needs.

36:08.946 --> 36:14.293
If he has God, there's nothing else that he needs in his life.

36:14.954 --> 36:16.136
Notice what he writes next.

36:17.157 --> 36:21.202
He says, he makes me lie down in green pastures.

36:22.242 --> 36:24.345
The key word here is makes.

36:25.827 --> 36:29.331
God made David lie down.

36:29.371 --> 36:35.880
David grew up as a shepherd, so he would have understood this, but there's this phenomenon with sheep called sheep bloat.

36:36.701 --> 36:37.702
I have to say this very carefully.

36:38.002 --> 36:41.507
Sheep bloat and sheep will just start to eat.

36:41.707 --> 36:47.194
They'll just eat, eat, eat, and they're eating so fast, their digestive system can't keep up.

36:47.214 --> 36:50.098
And when that happens to sheep, they start to bloat.

36:50.946 --> 36:57.496
And so a wise shepherd will notice this and they will come along and they will make the sheep lie down.

36:58.718 --> 37:02.203
Physically grab the sheep and make them lie down.

37:02.243 --> 37:03.225
You need to stop eating.

37:03.445 --> 37:04.687
You need to stop consuming.

37:04.968 --> 37:06.750
You need to rest.

37:07.532 --> 37:13.721
In his book, Gasping for Breath, author and pastor, David Johnson, tells about a time in his life when God made him lie down.

37:15.003 --> 37:16.025
He didn't want to lie down.

37:16.045 --> 37:16.946
He was made to lie down.

37:18.210 --> 37:19.312
He was a pastor of a church.

37:19.332 --> 37:20.453
It was growing like crazy.

37:20.493 --> 37:24.358
Everything seemed to be good on the outside, but on the inside, he was overwhelmed.

37:25.680 --> 37:27.563
On the inside, he was falling apart.

37:28.985 --> 37:33.211
And so his church board made him take a sabbatical.

37:33.231 --> 37:35.614
They made him lie down in green pastures.

37:35.894 --> 37:37.497
Here's what he writes about that experience.

37:38.598 --> 37:40.721
He said, I grew up thinking life works when you work.

37:41.943 --> 37:47.250
No pain, no gain, push harder, do more, keep going, never ever stop.

37:48.514 --> 37:49.516
But now I had to stop.

37:51.501 --> 37:52.623
I was forced to stop.

37:53.946 --> 37:56.111
Not just by the board, but by myself.

37:56.411 --> 37:57.614
I couldn't breathe.

37:58.656 --> 38:04.850
If I didn't figure out a way to recover my breath, I might be stopping for good.

38:05.986 --> 38:08.348
I met with a man one time, a godly man in our church.

38:08.368 --> 38:12.432
And when he was in his 20s, he was kind of a prodigy in the investment world.

38:12.472 --> 38:15.415
Everything he touched seemed to be the right investment to make.

38:15.455 --> 38:17.056
And so he was traveling a lot.

38:17.076 --> 38:19.439
He was working all the time, Monday through Friday.

38:20.660 --> 38:25.584
He told me when he would get to Saturday, he would try to wake up in the morning and he could not get out of bed.

38:27.186 --> 38:35.794
His adrenal glands were so shot, he would lie in bed Saturday and Sunday, and then he would get up Monday and he'd try to do it again.

38:37.794 --> 38:40.419
Finally, his wife came to him and said, enough.

38:41.300 --> 38:42.943
I'm not gonna live like this anymore.

38:44.266 --> 38:49.355
And so he made a decision that saved his marriage and saved his soul.

38:49.595 --> 38:51.478
He went to his boss and he said, I quit.

38:53.442 --> 38:54.905
Ended up starting his own business.

38:56.407 --> 38:58.030
Today, he's happily married.

38:58.090 --> 39:02.418
His business made more money than he was making for this other company.

39:03.650 --> 39:09.518
And most importantly, he has his soul back.

39:09.538 --> 39:11.801
Do you want to lie down or do you want to get knocked down?

39:13.464 --> 39:16.748
Do you want to slow down or do you want to fall down?

39:16.788 --> 39:22.857
Notice that God did not make David lie down because he was punishing David.

39:23.037 --> 39:26.602
He made David lie down because that was how he could restore his soul.

39:29.466 --> 39:32.210
Maybe you're in a season right now where God has made you lie down.

39:33.634 --> 39:34.796
It's been a health issue.

39:34.836 --> 39:39.562
You've lost something and so you don't have that in your life anymore.

39:39.963 --> 39:45.371
Maybe part of the purpose that God has in your life is to restore your soul.

39:46.512 --> 39:48.275
Here's the second way that God can restore your soul.

39:48.695 --> 39:49.617
Get on the right path.

39:51.980 --> 39:54.964
Here's what he says right after he says, he restores my soul.

39:55.045 --> 39:56.166
Here's what David writes next.

39:56.447 --> 40:01.714
He said, he God leads me in paths of righteousness.

40:03.170 --> 40:04.412
What path are you on right now?

40:06.817 --> 40:07.759
Because we're all on one.

40:09.181 --> 40:12.528
We all have a direction that our life is headed.

40:12.768 --> 40:19.481
If you were to describe to me the path that you're on in life, I could predictably say, here's where I think you're gonna be in 10 or 20 years.

40:20.924 --> 40:22.106
But here's the really good news.

40:22.406 --> 40:24.370
You can get on a different path.

40:25.154 --> 40:33.482
If you don't like the path that you're on right now, if it's not the path of righteousness, any moment you want, you can say, God, I want to get on a different path.

40:34.763 --> 40:39.508
And God in His mercy and grace can lead you to a different path in life.

40:41.050 --> 40:43.792
David says that God led Him to the path of righteousness.

40:44.913 --> 40:49.658
Wasn't so much that He got on the path of righteousness, it's that God led Him to it.

40:50.599 --> 40:53.842
I've been a pastor for over 25 years, and during that time, here's what I've discovered.

40:54.850 --> 40:56.291
Sin harms our soul.

40:58.734 --> 41:03.899
Sin harms our soul almost more than anything else.

41:03.919 --> 41:05.160
But here's what we do.

41:05.180 --> 41:06.682
We tend to think, oh, I can hide it.

41:07.983 --> 41:09.184
My parents aren't gonna find out.

41:09.685 --> 41:11.306
I mean, I got this whole thing figured out.

41:11.546 --> 41:12.728
My parents aren't gonna find out.

41:12.988 --> 41:14.469
My boss is not gonna find out.

41:14.690 --> 41:16.692
My neighbor, my friends, they will not find out.

41:18.253 --> 41:18.774
And guess what?

41:18.934 --> 41:20.135
Oftentimes, you're right.

41:20.415 --> 41:20.896
We're right.

41:22.097 --> 41:23.218
They don't find out.

41:24.578 --> 41:26.300
But here's what we underestimate.

41:26.701 --> 41:28.363
Sin changes us.

41:29.705 --> 41:31.347
Oftentimes, ever so slightly.

41:32.428 --> 41:37.315
And you know this is true because I guarantee you, you can think of someone that you remember going, you know what?

41:37.535 --> 41:39.558
What's different about them?

41:39.578 --> 41:40.879
They seem to be changing.

41:40.899 --> 41:42.081
I don't really know what it is.

41:42.101 --> 41:45.906
And then years later, months later, you found out, oh, they were doing that.

41:47.682 --> 41:54.211
They thought they were hiding it from you and you didn't know exactly what was going on, but you could see the effects of sin in their life.

41:54.271 --> 41:55.373
You could feel that.

41:57.376 --> 41:59.439
Are you on the path of righteousness right now?

42:01.942 --> 42:04.185
Maybe you've been wandering from the path of righteousness.

42:05.487 --> 42:09.212
Maybe you're in a dating relationship and it's pulling you off the path of righteousness.

42:09.473 --> 42:16.082
Maybe you have some friends in your life that you hang out with and they are pulling you off the path of righteousness.

42:18.530 --> 42:23.758
Two degrees of divergence today can lead up to a mile of distance in the future.

42:25.161 --> 42:27.044
Are you on the path of righteousness?

42:27.384 --> 42:30.930
Are you on the path that you want to be on?

42:32.112 --> 42:33.294
I had a deer hit my car.

42:34.916 --> 42:35.878
Yes, that's what happened.

42:35.918 --> 42:36.519
He hit me.

42:37.020 --> 42:37.801
I did not hit him.

42:37.821 --> 42:43.410
I was driving along Lexington with my daughter, and my daughter yelled out,

42:44.226 --> 42:51.715
And I looked, and on the side of the road, there was this huge buck, I mean, just large deer, which cracked me up, because it was hunting season.

42:52.616 --> 42:54.318
And all you hunters were up in Eley.

42:56.220 --> 43:02.327
Freezing your butt off, walking around in the woods, Elmer Fudd, looking for this big old deer, and he's mocking you.

43:03.048 --> 43:06.071
He's standing on the corner of Lexington.

43:07.953 --> 43:10.276
So my daughter yelled out, deer, and I kind of slowed down.

43:10.356 --> 43:11.858
I moved into the left lane.

43:12.098 --> 43:18.147
And the deer, I kind of saw him turn to go back into the cornfield and there was a car coming on a two lane in the opposite direction.

43:18.467 --> 43:26.860
And so I came back into my lane and boom, he smashed into the back of my car, just ran straight into it.

43:26.880 --> 43:33.309
If you look at my car right now, there's still deer hair in the passenger's door on the back.

43:33.329 --> 43:35.332
There's a huge dent underneath the window.

43:36.494 --> 43:39.378
And so I yelled out, what was that guy thinking?

43:41.026 --> 43:44.491
Which my daughter thought was funny, because she's like, he's a deer.

43:46.313 --> 43:48.115
And so she googled deer brains.

43:49.778 --> 43:52.481
And she said, dad, a deer has the brain of a one year old, okay?

43:52.521 --> 43:54.364
Just so you know what that guy was doing.

43:54.384 --> 43:55.886
And I was like, well, go figure, right?

43:56.907 --> 43:57.628
Makes sense to me.

43:58.649 --> 43:59.711
But what did that deer do?

44:01.213 --> 44:02.074
He took the wrong path.

44:03.736 --> 44:08.402
Standing on the side of the road, he looked across the road and there was something there that he just had to have.

44:09.122 --> 44:15.348
There's something there that he thought, you know what, I can't wait for traffic to go by, I gotta have it now, and I'm gonna be fine.

44:16.409 --> 44:17.631
I own big, strong deer.

44:18.972 --> 44:21.354
I think everything's gonna go work out just great.

44:21.595 --> 44:25.198
And he took the wrong path.

44:25.218 --> 44:29.783
You and I don't have the brain of a one-year-old, but the Bible says that we are like sheep.

44:31.044 --> 44:34.668
And I hate to break it to you, but sheep aren't all that smart.

44:34.688 --> 44:36.690
And so here's what we do, we go, I gotta have it.

44:37.922 --> 44:39.364
I have to have that now.

44:39.404 --> 44:42.850
That's going to make me so happy in my life.

44:44.893 --> 44:48.499
We take the wrong path and we crash.

44:50.142 --> 44:51.324
We crash a marriage.

44:51.585 --> 44:53.187
We crash a future.

44:53.468 --> 44:58.836
We crash our integrity, our good name, our reputation, a ministry that God has given to us.

44:58.917 --> 44:59.437
We crash.

45:01.180 --> 45:04.626
I'll hear people today use the phrase self care or your self care routine.

45:05.506 --> 45:13.018
And self-care is great, but let me just tell you, a bubble bath and candles is not going to take care of your deepest self.

45:13.038 --> 45:18.166
A new skincare routine and moisturizer is not going to take care of your deepest self.

45:19.688 --> 45:23.494
If you want self-care, get on the path of righteousness.

45:24.797 --> 45:28.062
Get on the right path with God.

45:28.943 --> 45:33.330
Here's the third way that God can restore our souls and it's to be still.

45:34.850 --> 45:35.711
Here's what David writes.

45:37.334 --> 45:41.321
He, God leads me besides still waters.

45:42.983 --> 45:45.608
He restores my soul.

45:46.910 --> 45:53.881
A little bit later in Psalm 46, it says, be still and know that I am God.

45:55.965 --> 46:00.773
I sat on my deck this summer and I started thinking through the attributes of God.

46:00.793 --> 46:01.554
He's holy.

46:02.594 --> 46:03.695
He's slow to anger.

46:03.735 --> 46:04.596
He's quick to love.

46:04.636 --> 46:06.458
He's everywhere, all at once.

46:06.518 --> 46:09.881
I started thinking through every attribute of God and I was still.

46:11.823 --> 46:13.104
And I just knew that he was God.

46:14.966 --> 46:18.490
Elsewhere in the Psalms, David is able to articulate how his soul is feeling.

46:18.730 --> 46:21.452
He says, my soul finds rest in God alone.

46:22.433 --> 46:24.295
My soul is in deep anguish.

46:25.116 --> 46:28.239
He writes, then my soul will rejoice in the Lord.

46:28.539 --> 46:31.282
And then a little later, he says, my soul is full of trouble.

46:31.874 --> 46:34.197
I am a man without strength.

46:36.520 --> 46:39.564
There's no pill for that.

46:39.584 --> 46:45.452
If your soul is full of trouble right now, if you feel like you have no strength, there's no pill for that.

46:47.535 --> 46:51.320
You have to be still and know that he is God.

46:52.301 --> 47:01.714
In 2018, there was a text alert that went out over the entire state of Hawaii that said a missile was en route to Hawaii and that people needed to take cover.

47:02.434 --> 47:12.687
You can imagine if you got this text message, people were panicking, people were calling loved ones, other people were calling friends they hadn't talked to in years, just because they wanted to ask them for forgiveness.

47:13.549 --> 47:15.191
They wanted to reconcile the relationship.

47:15.972 --> 47:20.398
People were praying and getting right with God and thinking about their eternity.

47:20.698 --> 47:27.727
And then 38 minutes later, another text message came out over the entire state of Hawaii and it said, false alarm.

47:29.409 --> 47:29.970
Oops.

47:31.266 --> 47:34.431
Can you imagine being the guy who made the mistake looking at the radar?

47:35.773 --> 47:36.454
Oh, you know what?

47:36.714 --> 47:37.596
That wasn't a missile.

47:37.616 --> 47:38.216
It was a goose.

47:39.438 --> 47:41.281
Yeah, it was just hard to tell, you know, sorry.

47:41.822 --> 47:43.404
Made a little mistake there, no big deal.

47:43.424 --> 47:44.907
Like, whoa, that's kind of a big deal.

47:45.948 --> 47:50.315
But for 38 minutes, the important became the urgent.

47:51.536 --> 47:57.866
For 38 minutes, people's souls started to come alive.

47:59.088 --> 48:00.530
A person can get right with God.

48:01.282 --> 48:05.368
A person's soul can begin to come alive in 38 minutes.

48:06.250 --> 48:07.832
In his book, it all goes back in the box.

48:09.194 --> 48:10.496
Author John Orberg writes this.

48:10.536 --> 48:16.044
He said, when Nancy and I got married, I asked her which household chore she most disliked.

48:17.306 --> 48:19.550
Her response was immediate, cleaning the bathrooms.

48:20.551 --> 48:22.695
John said, well, I'll take that off your plate.

48:22.935 --> 48:25.138
You'll never have to worry about that one.

48:26.100 --> 48:27.602
And he writes, she hasn't.

48:28.162 --> 48:32.008
In over 30 years of marriage, she's never cleaned the bathrooms.

48:33.311 --> 48:34.072
I haven't either.

48:34.112 --> 48:34.753
They're a mess.

48:39.741 --> 48:41.003
But at least we have more time.

48:44.109 --> 48:46.112
Now, this brings up an important point.

48:46.352 --> 48:47.334
Stuff needs to get done.

48:48.396 --> 48:52.082
I mean, I'm sure we would all just love to sit around and be still and know that he's God.

48:52.983 --> 48:54.546
But somebody's got to pick the kids up at school.

48:55.106 --> 48:57.128
Somebody's gotta go to Costco and get some food.

48:57.228 --> 49:00.171
Somebody's gotta bring the car in and get an oil change.

49:01.072 --> 49:05.596
We would love to just be still and know that he's God, but we have a life to live.

49:06.557 --> 49:09.580
When I was in college, I read a book by a monk named Brother Lawrence.

49:09.900 --> 49:11.782
It was called Practicing the Presence of God.

49:12.643 --> 49:15.966
And Brother Lawrence worked at this monastery as a dishwasher.

49:16.707 --> 49:18.889
He'd wash dishes, dry dishes.

49:19.169 --> 49:21.691
He would do this every day, not a real glamorous job.

49:23.113 --> 49:24.434
Here's what he writes in his book.

49:25.570 --> 49:40.934
He said, in the noise and clutter of my kitchen, while several persons are at the same time calling for different things, I possess God in His great of tranquility as if I were upon my knees at the last supper."

49:40.954 --> 49:43.398
Some of you are reading that like, what is he even talking about?

49:43.418 --> 49:45.121
He's a monk, so come some slack.

49:46.423 --> 49:47.244
But here's what he's saying.

49:48.446 --> 49:50.930
He's saying, when I'm in the kitchen doing the dishes,

49:51.586 --> 49:57.493
And there's people coming into the kitchen all the time and they're, you know, I'm gonna need some french fries and this person's upsetting us.

49:57.754 --> 49:59.115
It's like an episode of The Bear.

49:59.175 --> 50:02.600
I mean, it's just like, there's all kinds of conversation and things going on.

50:03.561 --> 50:05.323
He says, it's all of that's happening.

50:05.343 --> 50:06.885
I'm doing dishes and I'm praying.

50:08.667 --> 50:17.558
And I feel so close to God that it's almost as if I am sitting next to Jesus at the last supper.

50:18.920 --> 50:20.402
First Thessalonians, chapter five.

50:21.346 --> 50:22.808
says, pray without ceasing.

50:25.332 --> 50:26.954
Now, I don't pray without ceasing.

50:26.974 --> 50:29.999
You might think as a pastor, I'm just walking through the day, you know, I'm just praying at all times.

50:30.279 --> 50:33.584
Sometimes I'll be staring off into space and someone will be like, what are you doing?

50:33.684 --> 50:35.527
And just kind of kittingly, I'll be like, oh, I was praying.

50:36.408 --> 50:39.413
But I'm actually really thinking about, should the twins trade Byron Buxton?

50:39.453 --> 50:40.615
Should they call up Walker Jenkins?

50:40.655 --> 50:42.898
Like these are the kind of things rolling through my head.

50:42.918 --> 50:45.362
So I'm not praying without ceasing in that sense.

50:45.382 --> 50:46.964
But I don't think that's what Paul means.

50:48.046 --> 50:50.930
What Paul is saying is, pray throughout your day.

50:52.418 --> 50:54.700
You can pray in the car as you're going to pick the kids up.

50:56.262 --> 50:58.484
You can pray before you go into that meeting.

50:58.544 --> 51:02.148
You can pray as you're walking through Costco, maybe not out loud, but you can pray.

51:02.208 --> 51:06.212
You can pray as you're waiting for your oil to change.

51:06.432 --> 51:09.094
You can pray throughout your day.

51:09.915 --> 51:15.721
I was listening to a podcast and the speaker was talking about Tim Keller, who I quoted earlier, a pastor from New York.

51:15.941 --> 51:20.946
And he was talking about how Tim Keller has kind of based his daily routine around three things.

51:21.794 --> 51:24.137
morning, afternoon, and evening prayer.

51:25.279 --> 51:26.180
Every day, that was his routine.

51:26.200 --> 51:27.021
He would wake up in the morning.

51:27.221 --> 51:28.122
He would spend time with God.

51:28.142 --> 51:28.803
He would read the Bible.

51:28.823 --> 51:29.304
He would pray.

51:29.624 --> 51:32.528
And then at lunch, he would go take a walk around his neighborhood and just pray.

51:33.890 --> 51:36.654
And before bed, he would pause and you would say, God, thank you for this day.

51:37.895 --> 51:39.478
And I've tried to do the same thing.

51:39.518 --> 51:40.299
I wake up in the morning.

51:40.379 --> 51:40.819
I pray.

51:40.920 --> 51:41.701
I read my Bible.

51:41.761 --> 51:42.642
It's the first thing I do.

51:43.723 --> 51:46.407
And then I've started to come home from work, and I'll make a coffee.

51:47.308 --> 51:51.794
Now, those of you that know me, I had never drank coffee in my life until this July.

51:52.546 --> 51:53.467
I'm 47 years old.

51:53.687 --> 51:59.012
My taste buds were more wired to nerd clusters, sweet tart ropes, cotton candy.

51:59.032 --> 52:01.855
Then I was just kind of how my sweet butt, that's how I was wired.

52:01.915 --> 52:04.818
I finally started drinking coffee.

52:04.858 --> 52:05.719
I think I'm an adult.

52:05.739 --> 52:07.721
I think I became an adult at the age of 47.

52:09.223 --> 52:12.966
But I'll make a coffee and I'll just spend some time reading a chapter of a Christian book.

52:14.087 --> 52:18.131
It's been so good to decompress after the work day before I kind of engage with my kids.

52:19.192 --> 52:20.754
And then I always forget to do this.

52:21.474 --> 52:24.538
But before bed, I want to take a moment and say, God, thank you for today.

52:25.560 --> 52:26.821
Here's what I'm grateful for.

52:28.263 --> 52:31.488
What are the soul-carrying habits that you have built into your day?

52:32.469 --> 52:36.855
What are the soul-carrying habits that you have built into your week?

52:37.896 --> 52:39.198
Church is a soul-carrying habit.

52:40.379 --> 52:42.222
They did a study at Harvard University.

52:42.242 --> 52:43.023
Yes, that Harvard.

52:44.205 --> 52:51.154
And they found that people who regularly go to church, 29% less likely to be depressed

52:51.778 --> 53:03.456
50% less likely to be divorced, five times less likely to take their own life, and 33% less likely to die early or prematurely.

53:05.439 --> 53:06.761
They did a study of kids.

53:07.763 --> 53:15.154
They found that kids that regularly go to church when they're a kid, when they grow up, tend to be more forgiving

53:16.290 --> 53:22.236
have more purpose in life, have more joy and volunteer more and serve other people.

53:23.738 --> 53:24.619
That's the good news.

53:25.800 --> 53:32.807
The bad news is that when they ask people, do you regularly go to church and they say, yes, what they mean is generally I go to church once or twice a month.

53:33.888 --> 53:39.514
That when someone says, why I love that church, I go to that church, what they really mean is I'm actually going once maybe twice a month.

53:40.996 --> 53:43.378
I want you to think back on those statistics for just a moment.

53:44.610 --> 53:50.817
If you watch the Vikings, are you 29% less likely to be depressed?

53:58.645 --> 54:02.169
You're 29% more likely to be depressed, okay?

54:02.189 --> 54:05.653
I mean, I'll talk to people like, oh, I missed church, the Vikings game is on.

54:05.673 --> 54:07.715
It's like, how'd that go for you, huh?

54:07.735 --> 54:08.756
You feel good this afternoon?

54:08.796 --> 54:10.258
You feel really filled up from that?

54:13.026 --> 54:15.188
I mean, think about those statistics for kids.

54:17.090 --> 54:28.241
Is there anything that you could take them to do on the weekend that statistically speaking would lead to them in the future having more purpose, more joy, and serving other people?

54:28.481 --> 54:34.507
There is nothing that you could do on the weekend, statistically speaking, that would lead to those kind of attributes in the future.

54:36.149 --> 54:36.989
Here's the point.

54:37.290 --> 54:41.714
People with sole care habits built into their life, they flourish.

54:42.946 --> 54:43.747
They flourish.

54:45.248 --> 54:46.590
I want to take you back to Psalm 23.

54:49.873 --> 54:56.039
David says, even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

54:58.282 --> 54:59.723
There's two words I want to point out to you.

54:59.743 --> 55:00.704
The first one is through.

55:00.744 --> 55:05.349
You might be in a dark valley right now.

55:08.272 --> 55:10.514
You might feel like you're in a really dark place in your life.

55:12.898 --> 55:15.261
And I want to remind you that God's going to take you through it.

55:17.304 --> 55:18.686
This isn't the destination.

55:18.706 --> 55:19.887
This isn't where you're staying.

55:20.228 --> 55:22.251
God is going to take you through that valley.

55:22.271 --> 55:28.139
I was grabbing lunch just this week, and I've been to this restaurant enough to where I knew the woman who was serving.

55:28.179 --> 55:29.681
And so I said, hey, how have you been?

55:31.463 --> 55:34.327
And she said, well, I actually just went through a divorce a couple months ago.

55:34.407 --> 55:36.970
And it sounds like her husband was unfaithful.

55:38.693 --> 55:40.275
And she said, but I bought a study Bible.

55:41.617 --> 55:42.578
And I've been reading it.

55:43.394 --> 55:49.140
And her five-year-old's been reading the Bible and coming to church, and she looked at me and she said, I think we're doing pretty good.

55:51.041 --> 56:00.771
And I read this verse to her, that even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I said, God's gonna take you through this.

56:02.092 --> 56:06.717
The season that you're in right now, this dark place that you're in, it's not the destination.

56:06.957 --> 56:12.082
God's gonna bring you through it, that the God who led you to the valley is gonna lead you through the valley.

56:14.146 --> 56:16.929
The second word I wanted to point out to you was the word walk.

56:19.773 --> 56:25.119
When my kids were little, we had a basement and it wasn't totally finished and the kids would play down there during the day and they'd love it.

56:25.139 --> 56:26.661
There's a lot of space to run around and play.

56:27.042 --> 56:30.526
But at night, if I said to one of the kids, hey, you need to run downstairs and can you grab this for me?

56:31.487 --> 56:32.208
Well, they sprint.

56:33.349 --> 56:39.597
They sprint downstairs because it was dark and it was scary and they would get down there and get out as quick as they possibly could.

56:41.940 --> 56:43.602
If you're in a dark place in life right now,

56:46.082 --> 56:47.644
I want you to know that God is with you.

56:49.866 --> 56:52.989
You see, if I said to my kids, hey, I'll go with you.

56:53.009 --> 56:54.090
And I grabbed their hand.

56:54.611 --> 56:56.012
We didn't sprint down the basement.

56:57.513 --> 56:59.415
We would walk down the basement.

57:01.497 --> 57:04.260
And if you're in a dark place in life right now, God is with you.

57:06.202 --> 57:07.383
Grab onto his hand.

57:09.505 --> 57:10.526
You don't need to sprint.

57:10.546 --> 57:11.427
You don't need to fear.

57:13.329 --> 57:14.130
You can walk.

57:16.034 --> 57:19.618
But the God who led you to that valley is going to lead you through that valley.

57:19.819 --> 57:25.446
You can walk through this valley because he is with you.

57:27.588 --> 57:29.671
I want to close today by inviting you to take his hand.

57:31.834 --> 57:45.010
If you've never put your faith in Jesus Christ before, if you've been living your life just trying to fill up on Mountain Dew and all the things of this world, and you've just been misidentifying what's going to make you happy, I just want you to know when you put your faith in Jesus Christ,

57:46.146 --> 57:50.654
The Bible says when you confess with your lips and believe in your heart, you will be saved.

57:52.016 --> 57:56.383
You can't restore your soul without surrendering it to the one who created your soul.

57:57.946 --> 58:03.876
And so if you pray this prayer with me, would you take a moment after church to text the word begin to the number you see on the screen?

58:04.537 --> 58:05.439
Because we wanna know you.

58:06.681 --> 58:07.843
We wanna walk with you.

58:07.923 --> 58:10.728
We wanna help you get to know who Jesus is.

58:11.509 --> 58:12.210
Let's pray together.

58:17.730 --> 58:25.058
Lord, there might be someone here in church today who has never had a moment in their life where they've said, God, I surrender myself to you.

58:25.398 --> 58:27.681
I make you the Lord and Savior of my life.

58:31.204 --> 58:35.188
And God, maybe there's been chasing so many things and wanting so many other things and none of it satisfies.

58:38.952 --> 58:40.134
God, would you restore their soul?

58:42.016 --> 58:44.178
Would you restore their soul to yourself?

58:47.042 --> 58:49.404
God, they're gonna pray this prayer with me in the quietness of their mind.

58:49.424 --> 58:51.066
Lord, I confess my sins to you.

58:52.468 --> 58:53.108
I turn from them.

58:55.250 --> 59:00.796
I believe that Jesus Christ died on the cross to pay for my sins, to pay the penalty I could not pay.

59:01.196 --> 59:04.860
And so right now in this moment, God, I put my faith and my trust in Him.

59:07.563 --> 59:10.306
I ask that He would be the Lord and the shepherd of my life.

59:12.388 --> 59:14.450
And I receive the gift of eternal life.

59:17.282 --> 59:19.565
Lord, there might be others of us who are walking through a valley.

59:21.728 --> 59:23.650
And in some cases, it might be a very dark valley.

59:27.515 --> 59:28.456
God, would you take their hand?

59:31.200 --> 59:33.603
Would you remind them that they're not staying, that they're walking through it?

59:36.406 --> 59:39.410
And that God with you at their side, they don't need to run, they can

59:43.778 --> 59:47.986
Lord, would you restore our souls in the craziness and busyness of this season?

59:48.006 --> 59:51.233
God, would you lead us besides still waters?

59:53.216 --> 59:55.621
And would you God restore our soul?

59:57.685 --> 01:00:00.070
We pray all this in Jesus' name.

01:00:00.090 --> 01:00:00.370
Amen.

01:00:01.072 --> 01:00:03.597
Next week, we're gonna talk about Sabbath, which is really interesting topic.

01:00:03.617 --> 01:00:04.338
We will see you then.

